Spatial Distribution of Jobs From Major Locations

In [125]:
from adjustText import adjust_text
from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap
from geopy.geocoders import Nominatim
from geopy.exc import GeocoderTimedOut
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [126]:
geolocator = Nominatim(user_agent='Big_Data_Assignment')
geolocator.geocode('Australia')
def geocode_no_timeout(address):
    try:
        return geolocator.geocode(address)
    except GeocoderTimedOut:
        return geocode_no_timeout(address)
# get list of locations
df_locations = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Location','Latitude','Longitude'])
location_list = df[df['Location'].isna() == False]['Location'].unique()
location_cnts = df[df['Location'].isna() == False].groupby('Location').count()['Title']
missing = []
for location in location_list:
    coordinates = geocode_no_timeout(location)
    if (coordinates):
        df_locations.loc[len(df_locations.index)] = [location, coordinates.latitude, coordinates.longitude]
    else:
        missing.append(location)
# append job counts
df_locations['Count'] = df[(df['Location'].isna() == False) & ~(df['Location'].isin(missing))].groupby('Location').count()['Title'].values
df_locations = df_locations[df_locations['Latitude'] < 0]
In [127]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
aus_map = Basemap(projection='lcc', resolution='i', lat_0=-25.6, lon_0= 134.35, width=6.5E6, height=6.5E6)
aus_map.shadedrelief()
aus_map.drawcoastlines(color='gray')
aus_map.drawcountries(color='gray')
# convert coordinates from global to local and plot with labels
x, y = aus_map(df_locations['Longitude'].values, df_locations['Latitude'].values)
plt.scatter(x,y, s=df_locations['Count']/20, marker='o', c='red', alpha=0.8)
text = [plt.text(x[i]*(1+0.01), y[i]*(1+0.01), df_locations['Location'].values[i], fontsize=10) for i in range(len(x))]
adjust_text(text)
plt.title('Spatial Ditribution of Jobs From Major Locations', size=10)
legend = plt.legend(['Size = Volumne'], handlelength=0, handletextpad=0, fancybox=True)
legend.legendHandles[0].set_visible(False)
plt.show()

Evaluation:
Because the the value of data in 2019 has no detailed location, so this evaluation has 2 parts: in 2018 and 2019
- 2018: There are 3 kinds of trend:

  1. The number of jobs fall dramatically from 2018-10 to 2018-11 then began to increase slightly in 2018-12.
  2. The number of jobs fall from 2018-10 to 2018-11 then kept falling in 2018-12 but more slightly.
  3. The number of jobs fall from 2018-10 to 2018-11 then kept stable in 2018-12

- 2019: The number of jobs increased sharply from 2018-12 to 2019-01 then decreased until 2019-03

#create 3 array to save element
sectorArr = ['Sector']
subsector = ['SubSector']
value = ['Value']

#get max of each sector and save to the corresponding array
for sector in Spotlights.index.get_level_values(0).unique():
    if (sector == ' '):
        continue
    max = Spotlights[sector].max()
    sectorArr.append(sector)
    subsector.append(Spotlights[sector][Spotlights[sector] == max].index[0])
    value.append(max)

#create new series to contain result
result = pd.Series(value, index = [sectorArr, subsector])
result
